@startuml Project_IronLog_File_Change_Event

!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #1a1a2e
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #e94560
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #0f3460
skinparam sequenceParticipantBackgroundColor #16213e
skinparam sequenceParticipantFontColor #e0e0e0
skinparam sequenceGroupBackgroundColor #1a1a2e
skinparam noteFontColor #e0e0e0
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #0f3460
skinparam noteBorderColor #e94560

title Project IronLog — End-to-End File Change Event Sequence\n(Single Event Trace with Failure Path)

' ===== PARTICIPANTS =====

box "UNTRUSTED_ZONE — Monitored Endpoint" #1a1a2e
    participant "Filesystem\n(inotify/eBPF)" as FS
    participant "Edge Agent\n(Go, eBPF)" as Agent
end box

box "TRUSTED_ENCLAVE — HSM / SGX Boundary" #0d1b2a
    participant "HSM\n(FIPS 140-2 L3)" as HSM
    participant "SGX Enclave\n(Intel SGX)" as SGX
end box

box "STORAGE_ZONE — Off-Chain" #1a1a2e
    participant "Private IPFS\nCluster (≥3 nodes)" as IPFS
end box

box "LEDGER_ZONE — Permissioned Blockchain" #0d1b2a
    participant "Hyperledger Fabric\nPeer (Endorser)" as Peer
    participant "Smart Contract\n(Chaincode)" as CC
    participant "Orderer\nService" as Orderer
end box

box "AI_ZONE — Anomaly Detection" #1a1a2e
    participant "ML Inference\nEngine (ONNX)" as AI
end box

box "SIEM_ZONE — Security Operations" #0d1b2a
    participant "SIEM\n(Kafka → Splunk/Elastic)" as SIEM
end box

' ===== STARTUP — SELF-ATTESTATION =====

== AGENT STARTUP — SELF-ATTESTATION ==

note over Agent
  **CRYPTO OP: BLAKE3 self-hash**
  Agent computes BLAKE3 hash of its
  own binary at startup.
  **Threat mitigated:** T1036 (Masquerading),
  T1554 (Compromise Client Software Binary)
end note

Agent -> SGX : Request remote attestation\n(binary_hash, platform_evidence)
note right of SGX
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  UNTRUSTED_ZONE → TRUSTED_ENCLAVE
end note
SGX -> SGX : Verify platform integrity\n+ binary hash against allow-list
SGX --> Agent : Attestation token (signed, time-limited)
note over Agent
  Attestation token cached; re-attested
  every 15 min or on config change.
  **Threat mitigated:** Compromised agent binary
end note

Agent -> Agent : Unseal config from SGX-sealed storage\n(no plaintext credentials on disk)

' ===== MAIN FLOW — FILE CHANGE DETECTED =====

== FILE CHANGE EVENT — HAPPY PATH ==

FS -> Agent : eBPF event: file_modified(\n  path="/var/log/audit/audit.log",\n  pid=4821, uid=0, timestamp_ns)
note right of FS
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  Kernel space → User space
  eBPF preferred over inotify:
  inotify is bypassable via direct
  block device writes (T1006).
  **Threat mitigated:** T1070.002
  (Clear Linux Audit Logs)
end note

Agent -> Agent : Rate limiter check\n(token bucket: 1000 events/sec/agent)\nDrop if exceeded → emit metric

note over Agent
  **CRYPTO OP: BLAKE3 hash (high-throughput)**
  file_hash = BLAKE3(file_content)
  BLAKE3 chosen over SHA-256 for
  throughput: ~3× faster on x86-64.
  SHA-256 computed in parallel for
  compliance records requiring FIPS hash.
  **Threat mitigated:** T1565.001
  (Stored Data Manipulation)
end note

Agent -> Agent : Compute SHA-256 hash (parallel)\nsha256_hash = SHA256(file_content)

' --- IPFS PUSH (ENCRYPTED) ---

note over Agent
  **CRYPTO OP: AES-256-GCM encryption**
  encrypted_content = AES-256-GCM(
    key=HSM-derived-DEK,
    plaintext=file_content,
    aad=file_path || timestamp
  )
  CID alone proves existence, NOT
  confidentiality — encryption mandatory.
  **Threat mitigated:** T1530
  (Data from Cloud Storage Object)
end note

Agent -> HSM : Request DEK derivation\n(master_key_ref, context=file_path)
note right of HSM
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  UNTRUSTED_ZONE → TRUSTED_ENCLAVE
  **CRYPTO OP: HKDF key derivation**
end note
HSM --> Agent : DEK (ephemeral, never persisted)

Agent -> Agent : Encrypt file content with DEK\n(AES-256-GCM, 96-bit nonce)

Agent -> IPFS : PUT encrypted_content
note right of IPFS
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  UNTRUSTED_ZONE → STORAGE_ZONE
  Min replication factor: 3 nodes
  Pinning SLA: content pinned immediately,
  garbage collection exempted for
  compliance window (SOC2 = 7 years)
end note
IPFS --> Agent : CID (content-addressed hash)

' --- HSM SIGNING ---

note over Agent
  Construct payload:
  {
    file_path, blake3_hash, sha256_hash,
    timestamp (RFC3339Nano), ipfs_cid,
    dek_key_ref (NOT the key itself),
    agent_id, attestation_token_hash
  }
end note

Agent -> HSM : Sign(payload, agent_private_key_ref)
note right of HSM
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  UNTRUSTED_ZONE → TRUSTED_ENCLAVE
  **CRYPTO OP: ECDSA-P384 signature**
  Private key NEVER leaves HSM.
  **Threat mitigated:** T1552.004
  (Private Keys), T1588.004
  (Digital Certificates)
end note
HSM --> Agent : ECDSA-P384 signature

' --- BLOCKCHAIN COMMIT ---

Agent -> Peer : SubmitTransaction(\n  "LogFileChange",\n  signed_payload)
note right of Peer
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  UNTRUSTED_ZONE → LEDGER_ZONE
  mTLS channel, client cert
  verified against Fabric MSP.
end note

Peer -> CC : Invoke LogFileChange(signed_payload)

note over CC
  **ACCESS CONTROL CHECK:**
  1. Verify agent_id ∈ registered_agents
  2. Verify attestation_token is valid
     and not expired
  3. Verify ECDSA signature against
     agent's registered public key
  **CRYPTO OP: ECDSA-P384 verify**
  **Threat mitigated:** T1078
  (Valid Accounts — rogue agent)
end note

CC -> CC : Validate payload schema\n+ check for duplicate CID

CC -> CC : ZKP verification stub\n(VerifyCompliance — see below)

note over CC
  **CRYPTO OP: zk-SNARK verification**
  Verify proof π that:
    blake3_hash ∈ MerkleTree(allowed_hashes)
  "Compliance state" = Merkle root of
  authorized file hashes maintained
  by security policy contract.
  Using Groth16 (constant-time verify,
  trusted setup required).
  **Threat mitigated:** Unauthorized
  file modification passing validation
end note

CC --> CC : Emit event:\n  FileChangeRecorded{\n    txId, blockNum, timestamp,\n    agent_id, file_path,\n    severity, compliance_status\n  }

CC --> Peer : Transaction endorsed

Peer -> Orderer : Submit endorsed transaction
Orderer -> Orderer : Order into block\n(Raft consensus, 3-of-5 orderers)
note over Orderer
  **Endorsement policy:**
  3-of-5 organizations must endorse.
  **Threat mitigated:** T1195.002
  (Supply Chain Compromise —
  rogue single-org node)
end note

Orderer --> Peer : Block committed (block #N)

' --- AI ANALYSIS ---

Peer -> AI : Block event →\n  FileChangeRecorded event streamed\n  via Kafka topic
note right of AI
  **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
  LEDGER_ZONE → AI_ZONE
  Kafka topic with TLS + SASL auth
end note

note over AI
  **Feature vector extraction:**
  - cadence_delta: time since last
    change to this file
  - hour_entropy: Shannon entropy of
    change-hour distribution
  - process_lineage: pid → parent chain
  - user_context: uid, sudo history
  - file_sensitivity_tier: (1-5 scale)

  **Model: Isolation Forest (baseline)**
  Export: ONNX format
  Mode: Online (streaming) inference
  FP SLA: ≤ 0.1% on known-good patterns

  **Explainability output:**
  anomaly_score, triggered_features[],
  confidence_interval
end note

AI -> AI : Score event against\nIsolation Forest model

' ===== DECISION POINT =====

alt Anomaly Score ≤ Threshold (NORMAL)
    AI --> SIEM : Forward enriched event\n(anomaly_score=0.12, status=NORMAL)\nvia OpenTelemetry → Kafka
    note right of SIEM
      **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
      AI_ZONE → SIEM_ZONE
      Event indexed for audit trail.
    end note
    SIEM -> SIEM : Index event, update dashboard

else #ffcccc Anomaly Score > Threshold (ALERT)

    == FAILURE PATH — AI REJECTS COMMIT ==

    AI -> AI : Generate explainability report:\n  "Triggered features:\n   cadence_delta=4σ deviation,\n   hour_entropy=HIGH (03:17 UTC),\n   process_lineage=ANOMALOUS\n   (cron→bash→curl→tee)"

    AI --> SIEM : ALERT event\n(severity=CRITICAL,\n anomaly_score=0.94,\n triggered_features=[...],\n recommended_action=ISOLATE)
    note right of SIEM
      **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
      AI_ZONE → SIEM_ZONE
      Alert triggers PagerDuty/SOAR
    end note

    AI -> Peer : SubmitTransaction(\n  "FlagSuspiciousChange",\n  tx_id, anomaly_report)
    note right of Peer
      **TRUST BOUNDARY CROSSING:**
      AI_ZONE → LEDGER_ZONE
      Blockchain record is IMMUTABLE —
      the original FileChangeRecorded
      event remains. A new SuspiciousFlag
      event is appended referencing it.
      **Threat mitigated:** T1070
      (Indicator Removal — attacker
      cannot delete the audit trail)
    end note

    Peer -> CC : Invoke FlagSuspiciousChange(\n  original_tx_id,\n  anomaly_score,\n  explanation)
    CC -> CC : Mark record as UNDER_INVESTIGATION\nEmit SuspiciousChangeDetected event
    CC --> Peer : Transaction endorsed + committed

    SIEM -> SIEM : Trigger SOAR playbook:\n  1. Isolate endpoint (network quarantine)\n  2. Snapshot agent memory\n  3. Begin forensic collection\n  4. Notify SOC Tier-2

end

@enduml
